1 A. A street-legal, low-speed electrical vehicle or golf cart
2 operated on the streets and highways of this state shall be
3 registered as a motor vehicle.
4 B. The operator of a street-legal, low-speed electrical vehicle
5 or golf cart shall not be required to have an "M" endorsement on the
6 Class D license pursuant to Section 6-110.1 of Title 47 of the
7 Oklahoma Statutes. The operator shall be at least sixteen (16)
8 years of age and hold a valid Oklahoma driver license.
9 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 11-805.1, is
10 amended to read as follows:
11 Section 11-805.1. A. 1. No person shall operate any low-speed
12 electrical vehicle on any street or highway with a posted speed
13 limit greater than thirty-five (35) miles per hour.
14 2. Any low-speed electrical vehicle or golf cart shall be in
15 compliance with the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration
16 standards for low-speed vehicles in 49 C.F.R., Section 571.500, to
17 be operated on the road.
18 B. 1. If a golf cart is to be operated on any street or
19 highway with a posted speed limit no greater than thirty-five (35)
20 miles per hour, the golf cart shall have a vehicle identification
21 number.
22 2. Upon inspection by Service Oklahoma, a golf cart may be
23 registered as a motor vehicle and licensed through Service Oklahoma
24 if such golf cart has been converted into a street-legal vehicle
