1 meet ing all requirements in 49 C.F.R., Section 571.500, with the
2 exception that such golf cart shall not be required to have a
3 seventeen-digit vehicle identification number.
4 3. Service Oklahoma is authorized to promulgate rules for the
5 purposes of this act.
6 C. The provisions of subsection A of this section shall not
7 prohibit a low-speed vehicle from crossing a street or highway with
8 a posted speed limit greater than thirty-five (35) miles per hour.
9 C. D. This section shall not prevent a city from adopting any
10 ordinance that would further restrict low-speed electrical vehicles
11 from operating on certain city-owned streets in order to ensure the
12 public health and safety.
13 D. E. This section shall be a part of and supplemental to the
14 rules of the road as provided in Section 11-101 et seq. of Title 47
15 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title.
16 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
